# Vitest Unit Testing

Vitest + jsdom + Testing Library (`vitest.config.mts`, `vitest.setup.ts`).

## Conventions

- Colocate `*.test.ts` / `*.test.tsx` next to the module under test.
- Group with `describe`; use clear `it` names describing the scenario.
- Import `describe`, `it`, `expect`, `vi`, `beforeEach` from `vitest`.
- Mock at module boundaries (`getDb`, env helpers) — never hit live MongoDB.
- Query UI by role, label, or accessible name; assert user-visible behavior.
- Aim for 3–5 focused tests per file on critical paths.

## Mocking

```ts
vi.mock("@/lib/mongodb", () => ({ getDb: vi.fn() }));
```

Call `vi.clearAllMocks()` in `beforeEach` when mocks are shared.

## Fixtures

Use realistic `Movie` shapes — see `MovieCard.test.tsx`.
